            <title>[JCR-472] Wrap IllegalArgumentException from UUID when bad ID passed to Session.getNodeByUUID</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-472</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>Hi,&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
On 6/30/06, David Kennedy &amp;lt;&lt;a href=&apos;mailto:davek@us.ibm.com&apos;&gt;davek@us.ibm.com&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt; wrote:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; When invoking session.getNodeByUUID and passing an invalid ID, an&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; IllegalArgumentException is thrown.  Should this be wrapped in an&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; ItemNotFoundException or RepositoryException by SessionImpl?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Good point, an ItemNotFoundException would probably be best. Could you&lt;br/&gt;
please file a Jira issue for this?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
BR,&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Jukka Zitting</description>
